theorem closure_diff_frontier_eq_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure A \ frontier A = interior A := by
  -- Characterize the frontier as a difference of `closure` and `interior`.
  have hFront : (frontier A : Set X) = closure A \ interior A := by
    simpa using frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Prove the two inclusions.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `closure A \ frontier A ⊆ interior A`
    intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hx_cl, hx_notFront⟩
    -- If `x` were not in `interior A`, it would lie in the frontier,
    -- contradicting `hx_notFront`.
    by_cases hx_int : x ∈ interior A
    · exact hx_int
    ·
      have : x ∈ closure A \ interior A := ⟨hx_cl, hx_int⟩
      have : x ∈ frontier A := by
        simpa [hFront] using this
      exact False.elim (hx_notFront this)
  · -- `interior A ⊆ closure A \ frontier A`
    intro x hx_int
    have hx_cl : x ∈ closure A :=
      subset_closure (interior_subset hx_int)
    have hx_notFront : x ∉ frontier A := by
      intro hFrontMem
      have : x ∈ (interior A)ᶜ :=
        (frontier_subset_compl_interior (X := X) (A := A)) hFrontMem
      exact this hx_int
    exact ⟨hx_cl, hx_notFront⟩

theorem Set.compl_compl {α : Type*} {s : Set α} :
    ((sᶜ)ᶜ : Set α) = s := by
  ext x
  by_cases hx : x ∈ s
  · simp [hx]
  · simp [hx]

theorem frontier_eq_univ_of_dense_and_empty_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense A → interior A = (∅ : Set X) → frontier (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  intro hDense hInt
  -- Use the previously established description of the frontier of a dense set.
  have h :=
    dense_frontier_eq_compl_interior (X := X) (A := A) hDense
  -- Substitute the hypothesis `interior A = ∅` and simplify.
  simpa [hInt, Set.diff_empty] using h
